{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01V9dSVq7R44hZcW7AvRignC","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary with all the critical information:\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Analysis Report\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the ingestion service at `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion`, here's the complete breakdown:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **EntityController Structure**\n**File:** `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/controller/EntityController.java`\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Base path: `/api/v1/entities`\n- Dependency: `@Resource private EntityService entityService`\n- Methods:\n  - **POST** `/query` - Query failed entities with pagination\n    - Takes: `EntityQueryDTO req` (stage, code, pageNum, pageSize, sortKey, sortOrder)\n    - Returns: `ResultDTO<Pagination<Entity>>`\n  - **GET** `/{id}` - Retrieve single entity by ID\n    - Returns: `Entity`\n  - **GET** `/{id}/display-status` - Get entity display status with reprocess state mapping\n    - Returns: `ResultDTO<EntityStateDisplayDTO>`\n    - Maps `ReprocessState` (INIT, RUNNING, SUCCESS, FAILED, NONE) to display strings\n\n---\n\n### 2. **EntityService Interface & Implementation**\n**Files:** \n- Interface: `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/service/EntityService.java`\n- Implementation: `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/service/EntityServiceImpl.java`\n\n**Key Method Signatures:**\n```java\nEntity getById(Long id);\nvoid save(Entity entity);\nvoid saveBatch(Collection<Entity> entityList);\nboolean isInterrupted(long entityId);\nboolean setInterrupted(Long entityId, boolean interrupted);\nEntity getEntity(Long id);\nEntity getEntity(IngestionRequest req);\nPagination<Entity> queryFailedEntities(EntityQueryDTO req);\nboolean isProcessingFinished(Long entityId);\nboolean updateProcessingState(Entity fresh);\nList<Entity> findStuckEntities(Duration staleThreshold, int maxCount);\nMarkForReprocessResult markAllForReprocess();                    // KEY REPROCESS METHOD\nList<Long> findTopNIdsByReprocessState(ReprocessState state, int limit);\nEntityProcessLockInfo findProcessLockInfoById(Long id);\nboolean claimInitEntityForReprocess(Long id);\nboolean updateReprocessStateById(Long id, ReprocessState state);\n```\n\n**Critical Implementation Details:**\n- Uses `@Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)` for atomic state updates\n- `markAllForReprocess()` processes entities in batches (configurable via `policy.reprocess.mark-init-batch-size`, default 1000)\n- Each batch runs in its own transaction to prevent long-running transactions\n- Returns `MarkForReprocessResult` with `updatedCount`, `failedBatches`, `failedCount`\n- Implements rate limiting via token bucket in PolicyReprocessJob\n- Metrics tracking via MeterRegistry (counters, timers, gauges)\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Entity Model Definition**\n**File:** `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/entity/Entity.java`\n\n**Key Fields:**\n```java\n@Id Long id;\n@Enumerated EntityType type;              // HOST, USER_HOST_BINDING\nString source;                             // PORTAL, etc.\nString userId, hostId, adapterId;          // UUID strings\nString userIdentity, hostIdentity;         // identity strings (length 255)\nString bindingType;\nLocalDateTime bindingStartTime, bindingEndTime;\nString processingStage;                    // PENDING, ENFORCED, etc. (10 chars)\nInteger processingCode;                    // 0 = success, non-zero = failure\nString errorMessage;                       // 1024 chars max\n@JsonRawValue String processingResult;     // Large JSON blob\nInstant createdAt, updatedAt;\nboolean interrupted;\nString attributeFingerprint;               // 255 chars, not nullable\nString lastReqVersion;                     // 50 chars, not nullable\n@Enumerated ReprocessState reprocessState; // NONE, INIT, RUNNING, SUCCESS, FAILED (default: NONE)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Reprocess Patterns (grep results)**\n**Key Files Containing Reprocess Logic:**\n1. `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/service/EntityServiceImpl.java`\n2. `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/job/event/PolicyReprocessRequestedEvent.java`\n3. `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/job/PolicyReprocessJob.java`\n4. `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/controller/PolicyController.java`\n5. `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/controller/EntityController.java`\n6. `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/entity/Entity.java`\n\n**ReprocessState Enum Values (inferred from usage):**\n- `NONE` - Default state, no reprocessing\n- `INIT` - Marked for reprocessing, waiting to be claimed\n- `RUNNING` - Currently being reprocessed\n- `SUCCESS` - Reprocessing completed successfully (stage=ENFORCED, code=0)\n- `FAILED` - Reprocessing failed\n\n---\n\n### 5. **POST Endpoint Patterns in Controllers**\n\n**EntityController - POST `/query`**\n```java\n@PostMapping(\"/query\")\npublic ResultDTO<Pagination<Entity>> queryFailedEntities(@RequestBody EntityQueryDTO req) {\n    Pagination<Entity> page = entityService.queryFailedEntities(req);\n    return ResultDTO.success(page);\n}\n```\n\n**PolicyController - POST `/apply-existing-entities`** (KEY PATTERN)\n```java\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/api/v1/policy\")\n@RequiredArgsConstructor\n@Slf4j\npublic class PolicyController {\n    private final EntityService entityService;\n    private final ApplicationEventPublisher eventPublisher;\n\n    @PostMapping(\"/apply-existing-entities\")\n    public ResultDTO<MarkForReprocessResponse> applyExistingEntities() {\n        // 1.